    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-05-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="600"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d600">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-05-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your cable has been communicated to the Panama Government and withdrawal of their
                    request energetically urged. Panama unwilling to authorize payment to Morgan and
                    maintain that it has a right to have payment made to the commission which was
                    appointed as a result of your cable of April 30, complying with its request to
                    pay one million to Morgan and hold balance for their account.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
